Rebecca is a passionate Singer-Songwriter/Vocal coach/mentor /impressionist/photographer/creative junkie /self- development lover not a hater. 
 
“I want to motivate and inspire others to follow their dreams…corny? Well, maybe but it’s true. So what’s motivating me?? I had a huge tumour removed summer 2016. I am Rebecca and I am one heck of a passionate vocal coach/singer/songwriter/impressionist/health/fitness/self- improvement/anything that makes me smile!!  I love anything vocal/singing related and geek out on it every day.  I want to motivate and inspire others to follow their dreams…corny? Well maybe but it’s true. So what’s motivating me?? I had a huge tumour removed summer 2017 and my ovaries and fallopian tubes. The tumour was the size of a 20 week baby!!  However, despite not being able to walk for a couple of weeks, and feeling generally awful…. It has made me create and do what I love! It wasn’t an easy time but I won’t let fear dictate my life. I didn’t think ‘why me’, there are plenty of horrific issues people have to deal with…it’s not always smooth sailing.  It’s true when you hear, ‘Life is short’, the crazy thing is, I am glad it happened…I appreciate life even more and practice gratitude everyday…It’s so easy to get caught up with the little things…and I do sometimes, but look at the bigger picture, will it matter in a year or two…? 

Also thank you for all your support. It means a lot. 

Subscribe to Rebecca Vocal Athlete to get inspired by new videos weekly!!

Have a great day!!

Video Title: Surprising Beatboxing Twins Jake & Joemar (Reaction) | John Smulo
Video Description:
It's finally here! Today, we'll be going to Carcar Cebu to give the surprise gifts we bought from last week's episode to the beatbox twins Philippines, Jake and Joemar.

Hop on!

📣 If you want to support me and my mission, please consider joining our channel membership. You'll get access to perks such as loyalty badges, custom emojis, priority replies, exclusive live videos, and more! Join here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCKie0svsFyBBsKaQIA4hx-w/join 👈

On our way there, we randomly stopped by at this shop called Teology. It was great meeting employees who go out of their way to make customers feel at home.

Carcar is a beautiful place, and it's famous for its lechon, but I bought the twins and their family Jollibee instead since they're already in Carcar. I hope they enjoyed it.

Will Smith, Raffy Tulfo, and even Project Nightfall noticed Jake and Joemar's unique beatboxing skills and featured them on their social media channels. 

You can check their channel here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC3lMCWI6Pjb0sd5r-yM4apQ

The twins started beatboxing at five (5) years old, and they only learned to do so by listening to disco music and the radio!

We spent the day with them, and during the interview, they shared their future plans with us. Joemar wants to have their own studio and finish his studies, and Jake wants to become a drummer and a mixer. 

In addition to their excellent and unique beatboxing skills, what really amazed me is that when they first started earning from their YouTube channel, they helped their relatives build their own house. What a selfless thing to do, right?

So we asked the twins what they would want to get for themselves. 

And guess what? Bicycles!

Watch the full video to learn their reaction when they found out we brought them bicycles.

Thank you for taking the time to watch. Take care!

Video Title: Morissette AMON - Power [REACTION]
Video Description:
Morissette - Power (from Miss Universe Philippines, the FIRST TAKE from our recording session)

not a lot of people know that when I performed this at the MOA Arena for The Coronation of 2022 Miss Universe Philippines, we didn't have our session in the studio yet since I literally had just come from the U.S for our recent tour. standard practice would be we'd record a song to also somewhat master the track first before even performing it live, but this was an exemption. it also took us a while after then to finally get back into the studio due to the somewhat return of "normalcy" nowadays and getting ourselves loaded with work. 

we initially already had a date to record this track with my Kuya Kikx, but I was feeling under the weather and caught the flu which also affected my voice so we had to postpone. weeks passed and on this day, I was in the studio with Dave working on some stuff when I randomly said, "we should try to record 'Power' again." mind you, we had other plans that evening but this was just a "spur of the moment" kind of thing. perks of having our own studio, he opens the session and this right here was our very first take. of course we did several more after that and finished in just around 20 minutes. I decided to shoot with my phone just for memories sake, but this turned out better than we thought.. and just wanted to share this with all of you ♡

*PLEASE NOTE THAT THE OFFICIAL VERSION IS DIFFERENT FROM WHAT'S HEARD ON THIS VIDEO. this is just one take out of many we did that night, comped mixed and mastered for the best to be put out there. enjoy!

Video Title: TNT Boys The Beginning GGV (Reaction)
Video Description:
This is the TNT Boys, the beginning ggv reaction, how the TNT Boys Filipino Singing group started (also known as The Big Shot Trio). Subscribe to our channel here: https://goo.gl/Wto46s

Their members are as follows:
Keifer Sanchez, born 25 November 2004 (age 14) in Davao City, Philippines
Mackie Empuerto, born 8 September 2005 (age 13) in Manila, Philippines
Francis Concepcion, born 22 June 2006 (age 12) in Zamboanga, Philippines

On June 10, 2017, the Tawag ng Tanghalan Kids (TNT Kids) grand finals was held at Resorts World Manila. John Clyd Talili emerged as the grand champion, while Keifer Sanchez was declared runner-up, Mackie Empuerto in third place, and Francis Concepcion in fifth.

Vice Ganda was instrumental in forming the trio when the boys guested on his show Gandang Gabi Vice just after the grand finals. Vice asked them to have a singing battle with Beyoncé's "Listen". The boys' performance in Gandang Gabi Vice received critical acclaim and went viral on social media, with reaction videos from netizens praising their singing ability. There and then, Vice launched the kids as the TNT Boys.

That was the start of the TNT boys. They went on to do many other accomplishments:
Little Big Shots
Your Face Sounds Familiar Kids
President's Star Charity event
The Big Shot Concert' at the Araneta Coliseum
The World's Best

Awards: 
On November 14, 2018, the boys received the Royal Cub Award at the Rawr Awards 2018 from the entertainment blog

On November 29, 2018, they became recipients of the Rising Pop Child Performer of the Year Award at the PPOP Awards for Young Artists 2018.

Watch as I react to the TNT Boys together for the first time on GGV, doing a battle with “Listen” that would go on to form the TNT Boys. See how it all came together.  

This video they start their group as TNT Boys this video has gone viral and become popular around the world. "Tawag ng Tanghalan" (TNT) where their name as a group was derived...the little girl is Sheena Bellarmino.

The fourth boy, John Clyde, was the grand winner of the TNT Kids singing competition where Kiefer, Mackey, and Francis ended up as runner ups. He was supposed to join them- as all four of them were guests in the show after the competition- but he was sick at the time of guesting, so the host Vice Ganda thoughtfully set him aside (for him to rest for a while) in this mock singing battle. Clyde though was eager to take part in the singing as he asked the host- "What about me?"
